WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.875 --> 00:00:10.708
[slow instrumental music playing]

2
00:00:10.791 --> 00:00:12.208
[gate creaking]

3
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:20.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:00:31.916 --> 00:00:33.250
[Alba] <i>The day I was born</i>

5
00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:36.500
 <i>my grandma Clara saw my future.</i>

6
00:00:38.375 --> 00:00:41.708
 <i>And she said the stars had aligned</i>
 <i>to bestow me with gifts</i>

7
00:00:42.583 --> 00:00:45.000
 <i>that would overcome any terrible</i>
 <i>twists of fate.</i>

8
00:00:50.666 --> 00:00:52.041
 <i>But in time. I forgot.</i>

9
00:00:52.125 --> 00:00:53.958
[water pattering]

10
00:00:54.041 --> 00:00:55.208
[sobbing]

11
00:01:01.125 --> 00:01:04.250
[pensive music playing]

12
00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:10.541
[rattling]

13
00:01:16.541 --> 00:01:17.583
[gasps]

14
00:01:17.833 --> 00:01:19.000
Grandma.

15
00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:20.958
[gasps]

16
00:01:24.041 --> 00:01:28.916
[exhilarating instrumental music playing]

17
00:01:53.875 --> 00:01:54.791
[switch clicks]

18
00:02:23.625 --> 00:02:26.666
[captivating instrumental music playing]

19
00:02:31.458 --> 00:02:34.208
 <i>My grandmother wrote in her diaries</i>
 <i>that memory is fragile.</i>

20
00:02:36.708 --> 00:02:38.791
 <i>And the course of a life is so brief</i>

21
00:02:39.625 --> 00:02:42.208
 <i>that we fail to perceive</i>
 <i>the connection between events.</i>

22
00:02:44.416 --> 00:02:47.291
 <i>And we cannot measure</i>
 <i>the consequences of our actions.</i>

23
00:02:50.166 --> 00:02:51.416
[Alba grunts]

24
00:02:54.166 --> 00:02:55.250
[gasps softly]

25
00:03:00.416 --> 00:03:02.291
 <i>That's why ever since she was little.</i>

26
00:03:02.375 --> 00:03:05.708
 <i>my grandma recorded everything</i>
 <i>in hundreds of life diaries.</i>

27
00:03:07.916 --> 00:03:09.541
 <i>So that 50 years later.</i>

28
00:03:11.083 --> 00:03:12.708
 <i>I could use her writings</i>

29
00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:15.625
 <i>to reclaim the past.</i>

30
00:03:16.583 --> 00:03:19.083
 <i>and to overcome horrors of my own.</i>

31
00:03:23.291 --> 00:03:25.958
{\an8}[opening theme music playing]

32
00:04:34.166 --> 00:04:35.083
[creaks]

33
00:04:36.666 --> 00:04:37.625
[thuds]

34
00:04:44.333 --> 00:04:46.916
[Alba] <i>Clara del Valle. my grandma.</i>

35
00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:48.833
 <i>always had one foot in this world</i>

36
00:04:49.416 --> 00:04:51.041
 <i>and the other in the afterlife.</i>

37
00:04:51.125 --> 00:04:53.375
[Young Teresa] Give it back. please!
Give it to me!

38
00:04:53.458 --> 00:04:55.041
-You gave it to me!
-No. I did not!

39
00:04:55.125 --> 00:04:56.666
[indistinct shouting]

40
00:04:56.750 --> 00:04:59.291
Give it back! Stop that!
Give it back!

41
00:04:59.375 --> 00:05:01.166
Knock it off! Mom said you should hurry!

42
00:05:01.250 --> 00:05:02.666
-I asked for it yesterday.
-No!

43
00:05:02.750 --> 00:05:04.750
-[arguing continues]
-What on God's green earth

44
00:05:04.833 --> 00:05:07.208
-are you all doing here? Huh?
-[Young Luis] It's mine!

45
00:05:07.291 --> 00:05:10.125
Didn't I already tell you
to go get dressed? Now. go!

46
00:05:10.208 --> 00:05:14.666
And you. Clarita. you also have to get
ready for mass. my child.

47
00:05:14.750 --> 00:05:16.875
-[sighs in exasperation] Ay. ay. ay.
-I won't go.

48
00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:18.666
You can't stay here.

49
00:05:19.125 --> 00:05:21.000
You don't get to make the rules.
young lady.

50
00:05:21.083 --> 00:05:23.166
[indistinct shouting]

51
00:05:23.250 --> 00:05:27.333
[Nana] Oh. Lord. These kids think
the house tidies up after itself!

52
00:05:27.416 --> 00:05:29.833
Ugh! Sweetie! Go over there.

53
00:05:29.916 --> 00:05:31.666
You're going to end up all sweaty!

54
00:05:31.750 --> 00:05:32.958
Nana. help me.

55
00:05:33.041 --> 00:05:34.791
God. I'm running late for mass.

56
00:05:35.916 --> 00:05:37.833
[Alba] <i>Clara developed her psychic powers</i>

57
00:05:38.416 --> 00:05:40.833
 <i>with encouragement from her beloved</i>
 <i>Uncle Marcos.</i>

58
00:05:41.458 --> 00:05:42.791
 <i>an insatiable explorer</i>

59
00:05:42.875 --> 00:05:45.666
 <i>who gathered esoteric knowledge</i>
 <i>from all over the world.</i>

60
00:05:47.833 --> 00:05:48.708
I won't go to mass.

61
00:05:49.208 --> 00:05:51.625
-Why not?
-Uncle Marcos is on his way.

62
00:05:52.250 --> 00:05:54.750
Sweetie. Uncle Marcos is still travelling.

63
00:05:54.833 --> 00:05:56.291
He's far far away.

64
00:05:56.625 --> 00:05:58.166
I know. But he's coming.

65
00:05:58.250 --> 00:06:00.666
And I wanna be home
when he gets here.

66
00:06:00.750 --> 00:06:01.750
Rosa!

67
00:06:02.208 --> 00:06:03.083
I have no idea.

68
00:06:13.125 --> 00:06:15.500
[Alba] <i>Her older sister. Rosa.</i>

69
00:06:15.875 --> 00:06:19.166
 <i>was the only one who really understood</i>
 <i>Clara's eccentricities.</i>

70
00:06:19.750 --> 00:06:22.500
 <i>Maybe because she didn't belong</i>
 <i>to this world. either.</i>

71
00:06:28.833 --> 00:06:30.875
This place is great to hide out in.

72
00:06:30.958 --> 00:06:32.583
These creatures are gonna protect it.

73
00:06:33.541 --> 00:06:35.166
Can you tell me why we're hiding now?

74
00:06:35.541 --> 00:06:37.500
I don't get why we have to go to mass.

75
00:06:38.041 --> 00:06:40.625
Mom says we can speak to God directly
if we want.

76
00:06:40.708 --> 00:06:41.916
[chuckles] Right.

77
00:06:42.500 --> 00:06:43.750
I'm gonna tell you a secret.

78
00:06:44.750 --> 00:06:48.166
There's a lot of things in this world
I'll never understand.

79
00:06:48.250 --> 00:06:50.500
But I've reached the conclusion
that it's because

80
00:06:50.791 --> 00:06:52.375
some are just illogical.

81
00:06:52.833 --> 00:06:54.916
Don't you think you're a little old
for this?

82
00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:56.666
[all laughing]

83
00:06:57.041 --> 00:06:59.000
Dad. if you're talking
about my embroidery.

84
00:06:59.333 --> 00:07:01.875
I'm not going to stop
until it's the biggest

85
00:07:02.166 --> 00:07:04.166
-table cloth in the world.
-Time to go.

86
00:07:04.541 --> 00:07:08.500
-[indistinct chatter]
-[bell tolling]

87
00:07:13.666 --> 00:07:16.833
-[man] Good morning.
-Hello. ladies. How are you?

88
00:07:16.916 --> 00:07:18.791
Thank you. hi.

89
00:07:18.875 --> 00:07:19.958
How are you?

90
00:07:21.125 --> 00:07:22.125
Good morning.

91
00:07:22.208 --> 00:07:23.916
Great entrance. candidate.

92
00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:25.583
-Nivea.
-Hello. Good to see you.

93
00:07:25.666 --> 00:07:26.666
-Good morning.
-Please.

94
00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:28.833
I reserved the third row
so we can sit together.

95
00:07:28.916 --> 00:07:30.208
-Perfect.
-It was nothing.

96
00:07:30.291 --> 00:07:31.583
Excuse me.

97
00:07:31.666 --> 00:07:33.250
No. no. no. Please don't.

98
00:07:34.458 --> 00:07:36.958
Honey. look. they're watching us.
It's not normal.

99
00:07:37.041 --> 00:07:40.333
Well. get accustomed to it. It'll be worse
when you're elected senator.

100
00:07:41.083 --> 00:07:43.875
[Father Restrepo] On this holy Thursday.
we had to enter penance

101
00:07:43.958 --> 00:07:46.375
remembering the day when Jesus Christ

102
00:07:46.458 --> 00:07:49.625
the son of God.
gave his life for our sins.

103
00:07:49.708 --> 00:07:51.416
-So it is. brothers and sisters--
-Dad?

104
00:07:52.375 --> 00:07:53.583
-Hmm?
-Good thing they put

105
00:07:53.666 --> 00:07:54.916
the covers on the saints.

106
00:07:55.000 --> 00:07:57.250
Because the blood they paint on them
is disgusting.

107
00:07:57.708 --> 00:07:59.291
Shh! Pay attention. Clara.

108
00:07:59.666 --> 00:08:02.416
[Father Restrepo continues indistinctly]

109
00:08:02.500 --> 00:08:04.583
[woman 1] Oh. my God. look at Rosa.

110
00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:07.250
She's from another planet. right?

111
00:08:07.333 --> 00:08:08.625
[woman 1] She's an angel.

112
00:08:09.083 --> 00:08:10.500
Or a mermaid.

113
00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:17.375
[enchanting instrumental music playing]

114
00:08:17.458 --> 00:08:19.416
[Father Restrepo] And now
Hell awaits us all

115
00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:23.083
unless we turn back in repentance…
[continues indistinctly]

116
00:08:23.166 --> 00:08:24.833
[man] Unbelievable!

117
00:08:24.916 --> 00:08:26.541
After all this time.

118
00:08:26.791 --> 00:08:28.333
they keep selling us the story

119
00:08:28.875 --> 00:08:30.791
of Hell as if it were fresh bread!

120
00:08:35.041 --> 00:08:36.666
Why the sad look. Clara?

121
00:08:37.416 --> 00:08:39.041
-Should I leave now?
-No!

122
00:08:39.541 --> 00:08:41.416
-[shushes]
-[indistinct chatter]

123
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.333
Oh. my God. Who is she talking to?

124
00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:47.708
I really miss you. Uncle Marcos.

125
00:08:48.458 --> 00:08:49.791
Look at the bright side.

126
00:08:49.875 --> 00:08:52.666
Now. I don't have to get on a boat
to come see you.

127
00:08:53.208 --> 00:08:55.916
I just have to do this. [clicks fingers]
And voila!

128
00:08:56.333 --> 00:08:57.833
Isn't it great? [chuckles]

129
00:08:58.541 --> 00:09:01.875
Barrabás! Release. Barrabás!
Release. Barrabás!

130
00:09:01.958 --> 00:09:03.791
Have you practiced your powers?

131
00:09:06.125 --> 00:09:08.458
[gasps] Many of the living

132
00:09:08.666 --> 00:09:11.416
would give anything
to do what we can.

133
00:09:12.291 --> 00:09:13.750
You're special. Clara.

134
00:09:14.541 --> 00:09:16.166
You're gonna help so many people.

135
00:09:16.750 --> 00:09:19.291
A horde of pure sinners saved him.

136
00:09:19.583 --> 00:09:21.250
saved Barrabás from the fires of Hell.

137
00:09:21.708 --> 00:09:23.708
[gasps. groans]

138
00:09:23.791 --> 00:09:25.583
Which one do you want me
to release?

139
00:09:25.666 --> 00:09:28.083
The chief priests and the elders.

140
00:09:28.166 --> 00:09:30.291
they suggested the multitude

141
00:09:30.375 --> 00:09:33.250
-to choose Barrabás. to save Barrabás…
-[blabbering]

142
00:09:33.333 --> 00:09:35.000
-[chuckling]
-…standing in opposition

143
00:09:35.125 --> 00:09:37.000
to those who called
for Christ's salvation.

144
00:09:38.041 --> 00:09:40.125
That is why the bandit Barrabás was saved.

145
00:09:40.416 --> 00:09:44.458
That's why. that is the reason why
every one of you sinners must do penance

146
00:09:44.541 --> 00:09:46.416
or you'll spend the rest of eternity

147
00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:48.083
burning in the flames of Hell.

148
00:09:48.166 --> 00:09:50.333
Straight to Hell!

149
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:53.625
Back then. the… [clears throat]

150
00:09:53.708 --> 00:09:54.958
[indistinct chatter]

151
00:09:55.666 --> 00:09:58.875
Father Restrepo.
what if Hell doesn't exist?

152
00:09:58.958 --> 00:10:00.541
[Father] What are you saying. brat?

153
00:10:00.666 --> 00:10:02.416
What did you say?

154
00:10:02.625 --> 00:10:05.916
Well. you've never been dead. so.
you can't possibly know

155
00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:08.791
-what's on the other side.
-You must be possessed by the Devil!

156
00:10:08.875 --> 00:10:11.833
[indistinct chatter]

157
00:10:12.208 --> 00:10:13.583
[Father] She is possessed!

158
00:10:13.791 --> 00:10:16.666
Madness! Prideful!

159
00:10:16.750 --> 00:10:18.041
Father!

160
00:10:18.125 --> 00:10:20.833
That girl is possessed by the Devil!
Be gone!

161
00:10:21.083 --> 00:10:22.833
Only a fanatic like Father Restrepo

162
00:10:22.916 --> 00:10:25.208
can still believe in the Devil
in the 20th century.

163
00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:26.708
Yes. but that's not the point.

164
00:10:26.791 --> 00:10:29.708
The point is if they find out about
Clarita's exploits.

165
00:10:29.791 --> 00:10:31.291
people will start gossiping.

166
00:10:31.375 --> 00:10:33.791
My candidacy for the Liberal Party
has gone to hell.

167
00:10:33.875 --> 00:10:35.166
Oh. don't exaggerate.

168
00:10:35.250 --> 00:10:38.083
[Severo] I can't deal with people talking
about my family.

169
00:10:38.166 --> 00:10:40.333
We've had enough of your brother.

170
00:10:40.416 --> 00:10:44.000
No. I'm not gonna let you blame Marcos
for every little thing that comes to mind.

171
00:10:44.083 --> 00:10:46.208
[Severo] I knew he'd be
a bad influence on Clara.

172
00:10:46.291 --> 00:10:48.875
-And now--
-Careful what you say. Severo del Valle!

173
00:10:49.458 --> 00:10:53.458
Remember that our family will always be
more important than our personal agendas.

174
00:10:53.541 --> 00:10:55.000
Don't you forget that.

175
00:10:55.083 --> 00:10:57.291
And we love Clarita
just the way she is.

176
00:10:57.375 --> 00:10:58.666
[engine starts]

177
00:11:06.083 --> 00:11:09.333
I'm so hungry! I need to eat now!

178
00:11:10.791 --> 00:11:12.625
-Teresa!
-Stop that. Ana!

179
00:11:12.708 --> 00:11:14.250
-No. Ana. no!
-Wait. my leg!

180
00:11:14.333 --> 00:11:15.791
She's so annoying!

181
00:11:16.958 --> 00:11:18.416
[Young Teresa] Mom. who are they?

182
00:11:18.500 --> 00:11:20.625
-Uncle Marcos?
-[Young Luis] It's Uncle Marcos!

183
00:11:20.708 --> 00:11:22.833
-[Nivea] Marcos!
-[child] Who is it?

184
00:11:23.041 --> 00:11:24.750
You-- Your brother's here.

185
00:11:24.833 --> 00:11:27.333
I mean… your brother's body.

186
00:11:28.750 --> 00:11:30.500
-No!
-What is it?

187
00:11:30.583 --> 00:11:31.958
Nana! Nana!

188
00:11:40.791 --> 00:11:42.666
[breath trembling] Marcos?

189
00:11:43.583 --> 00:11:44.750
Open it!

190
00:11:45.083 --> 00:11:48.083
[Alba] <i>That was how Uncle Marcos</i>
 <i>returned from his last trip.</i>

191
00:11:48.958 --> 00:11:51.375
 <i>He'd been killed by a mysterious</i>
 <i>African disease</i>

192
00:11:51.458 --> 00:11:54.958
 <i>that made you wrinkled and yellowed.</i>
 <i>like papyrus.</i>

193
00:11:55.041 --> 00:11:56.791
[Nana] Clarita told us he was coming.

194
00:11:57.375 --> 00:12:01.875
-[somber instrumental music playing]
-[sobbing]

195
00:12:04.583 --> 00:12:06.166
[dog barking]

196
00:12:07.250 --> 00:12:10.375
[dog barking and whimpering]

197
00:12:22.791 --> 00:12:24.000
Rosa!

198
00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:28.291
A little dog!

199
00:12:31.458 --> 00:12:32.666
How are you doing?

200
00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:36.541
-Oh!
-Oh!

201
00:12:37.041 --> 00:12:39.583
-It's all right.
-[dog whimpering]

202
00:12:40.291 --> 00:12:41.625
-He's so tiny.
-Barrabás.

203
00:12:42.166 --> 00:12:43.333
[Rosa chuckles]

204
00:12:49.125 --> 00:12:51.875
[Alba] <i>That would've been</i>
 <i>one of the saddest days of her life</i>

205
00:12:52.625 --> 00:12:55.708
 <i>if Barrabás hadn't arrived</i>
 <i>with Uncle Marcos's possessions</i>

206
00:12:56.375 --> 00:13:00.666
 <i>and Rosa hadn't been by her side</i>
 <i>supporting her.</i>

207
00:13:01.166 --> 00:13:03.291
[keys clacking]

208
00:13:03.666 --> 00:13:06.166
-[Young Clara] Oh!
-Clarita…

209
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:09.625
Uncle Marcos brought so many books.

210
00:13:10.458 --> 00:13:11.541
Take a peek.

211
00:13:11.625 --> 00:13:13.166
-[chuckles]
-[Barrabás whimpers]

212
00:13:13.250 --> 00:13:15.708
He wrote down all of his adventures.

213
00:13:15.791 --> 00:13:17.625
-Look. Paris!
-Wow!

214
00:13:18.708 --> 00:13:22.500
Clara. you could follow
in his footsteps. right?

215
00:13:23.083 --> 00:13:24.541
Write down your adventures.

216
00:13:25.708 --> 00:13:26.833
Here's a little diary.

217
00:13:27.583 --> 00:13:30.000
It's brand new. [exhales] Look.

218
00:13:31.166 --> 00:13:35.291
[soft instrumental music playing]

219
00:13:43.791 --> 00:13:45.875
-Thank you.
-Any time.

220
00:13:59.375 --> 00:14:02.083
[Alba] <i>Barrabás came into the family</i>
 <i>by sea.</i>

221
00:14:02.916 --> 00:14:06.375
 <i>Those were the first words my grandma</i>
 <i>wrote in her life diaries.</i>

222
00:14:07.375 --> 00:14:08.750
 <i>as she liked to call them.</i>

223
00:14:19.750 --> 00:14:22.125
[Severo] That is called bribery.
and it's a crime.

224
00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:25.333
[advisor] In this country.

225
00:14:25.416 --> 00:14:28.750
all of the most respected senators
got into Congress in this manner.

226
00:14:30.125 --> 00:14:31.125
But I'm a lawyer.

227
00:14:32.541 --> 00:14:34.875
My job is to protect laws
and prevent abuses

228
00:14:34.958 --> 00:14:36.500
exactly like this from occurring.

229
00:14:36.791 --> 00:14:39.833
Well. the scandal on this past
holy Thursday

230
00:14:39.916 --> 00:14:41.291
didn't go over well. my friend.

231
00:14:41.375 --> 00:14:43.500
And we're on the verge of the elections.

232
00:14:47.125 --> 00:14:49.958
Look. I promised my wife that
if I did this. I'd play fair.

233
00:14:50.500 --> 00:14:54.375
Well. if just keeping her happy
is what you need.

234
00:14:55.458 --> 00:14:56.416
this is the best way.

235
00:14:57.500 --> 00:14:59.416
No other man except you

236
00:14:59.500 --> 00:15:02.291
will push forward the petition
of the suffragettes.

237
00:15:03.916 --> 00:15:05.833
[woman] <i>We have to talk</i>
 <i>to the real people.</i>

238
00:15:06.291 --> 00:15:07.708
With the town's people.

239
00:15:07.833 --> 00:15:10.833
And go door to door.
break into the factory

240
00:15:11.291 --> 00:15:12.791
and really make some noise.

241
00:15:12.916 --> 00:15:14.708
[Nivea] If my husband is elected senator.

242
00:15:14.791 --> 00:15:17.166
we'll be able to make these changes
from Congress.

243
00:15:17.291 --> 00:15:19.416
Maybe. if your husband
were a woman. like us.

244
00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:20.500
[all chuckling]

245
00:15:20.583 --> 00:15:22.291
[woman 2] We want others
to make changes

246
00:15:22.375 --> 00:15:25.000
and we haven't even thought
about taking off our corsets.

247
00:15:25.083 --> 00:15:26.625
You take it off now!

248
00:15:26.708 --> 00:15:29.333
-[all laughing]
-[woman 1] My God. this child!

249
00:15:29.416 --> 00:15:31.458
-Senora.
-She's the young--

250
00:15:31.541 --> 00:15:33.791
Look. Another letter for Rosa.

251
00:15:33.875 --> 00:15:35.791
Hmm. Thank you. Nana.

252
00:15:35.875 --> 00:15:39.166
-Mom. may I see it?
-No.

253
00:15:39.625 --> 00:15:41.375
From Ester Trueba's son?

254
00:15:41.458 --> 00:15:44.041
[Nivea] Yes. the young man secured
a claim for a gold mine.

255
00:15:44.125 --> 00:15:46.250
Poor guy. he's been mining
for almost two years.

256
00:15:46.333 --> 00:15:48.083
-[woman 2] That long?
-Well. why. Mommy?

257
00:15:48.166 --> 00:15:51.708
Because he's a man who's very determined
and I really like that.

258
00:15:51.791 --> 00:15:54.541
Right? Because when a woman's
as beautiful as Rosa.

259
00:15:55.458 --> 00:15:57.875
men are too timid to even approach her.

260
00:16:00.125 --> 00:16:01.416
Thank you.

261
00:16:02.083 --> 00:16:03.375
Look.

262
00:16:03.458 --> 00:16:05.250
Oh. it's beautiful. Clarita.

263
00:16:05.333 --> 00:16:07.125
-Can we buy it. Rosa?
-Let's see.

264
00:16:18.125 --> 00:16:19.041
[chuckles softly]

265
00:16:22.291 --> 00:16:23.708
[Nana] Come on. girls. let's go.

266
00:16:23.958 --> 00:16:26.750
Oh! Shoo! Shoo! Shoo!
Always stalking Rosita!

267
00:16:26.958 --> 00:16:28.125
Savages!

268
00:16:29.333 --> 00:16:30.708
Hurry up. girls.

269
00:16:35.541 --> 00:16:36.583
Excuse me.

270
00:16:39.875 --> 00:16:41.000
What's your name?

271
00:16:41.666 --> 00:16:42.916
Who wants to know?

272
00:16:44.333 --> 00:16:45.500
Esteban Trueba.

273
00:16:46.416 --> 00:16:48.875
Keep walking. or I won't hear
the end of it.

274
00:16:51.416 --> 00:16:53.500
Her name is Rosa del Valle!

275
00:16:53.583 --> 00:16:55.625
And she has nobody else courting her!

276
00:16:55.708 --> 00:16:57.000
-Clara!
-Clara!

277
00:16:57.083 --> 00:16:58.375
[Young Clara chuckling]

278
00:16:59.458 --> 00:17:00.541
Rosa.

279
00:17:04.958 --> 00:17:06.208
[Alba] <i>That afternoon.</i>

280
00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:09.375
 <i>the beautiful Rosa entered</i>
 <i>Esteban Trueba's life</i>

281
00:17:09.500 --> 00:17:12.125
 <i>like a distracted angel stealing his soul.</i>

282
00:17:14.208 --> 00:17:15.833
 <i>And from then on.</i>

283
00:17:16.208 --> 00:17:19.166
 <i>he promised himself that he'd do</i>
 <i>anything he could</i>

284
00:17:19.541 --> 00:17:21.083
 <i>to become a wealthy man.</i>

285
00:17:21.583 --> 00:17:23.666
 <i>worthy of taking her to the altar.</i>

286
00:17:30.208 --> 00:17:32.875
-[breathing heavily]
-[piano music playing]

287
00:17:32.958 --> 00:17:34.833
Rosa! Another letter!

288
00:17:34.916 --> 00:17:36.125
May I read it?

289
00:17:37.125 --> 00:17:38.583
"My beloved beautiful Rosa.

290
00:17:38.750 --> 00:17:40.333
-the--"
-Give me that.

291
00:17:41.583 --> 00:17:43.666
"The seconds here are endless
without you."

292
00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:45.208
[gasps]

293
00:17:45.291 --> 00:17:48.083
I want someone to love me as much
as Esteban loves Rosa.

294
00:17:48.166 --> 00:17:50.708
I still don't understand
what love has to do

295
00:17:50.791 --> 00:17:53.125
with mining a bunch of rocks
to get rich.

296
00:17:53.416 --> 00:17:55.041
Because he adores you!

297
00:17:55.125 --> 00:17:57.291
-I don't want gold.
-Neither do I.

298
00:17:57.375 --> 00:17:59.833
Don't you want somebody
to give you a house like this?

299
00:18:00.583 --> 00:18:02.583
-No.
-What do you mean?

300
00:18:03.750 --> 00:18:05.583
You'll live off of your
made-up creatures?

301
00:18:05.666 --> 00:18:07.083
Maybe.

302
00:18:07.458 --> 00:18:08.708
I want that. too.

303
00:18:09.125 --> 00:18:11.583
-[Young Luis] I don't get it.
-You want that. too?

304
00:18:12.166 --> 00:18:14.500
[music playing]

305
00:18:21.875 --> 00:18:23.375
-[Young Clara] Barrabás!
-[barking]

306
00:18:23.458 --> 00:18:24.666
[Alba]<i> For Clara.</i>

307
00:18:24.750 --> 00:18:26.791
 <i>time passed with nothing more note-worthy</i>

308
00:18:26.875 --> 00:18:29.375
 <i>than the limitless growth</i>
 <i>of her dog Barrabás.</i>

309
00:18:32.500 --> 00:18:36.375
 <i>Popular fantasy and ignorance</i>
 <i>regarding his breed</i>

310
00:18:36.458 --> 00:18:39.583
 <i>led to attributing him</i>
 <i>with mythological characteristics.</i>

311
00:18:41.458 --> 00:18:42.916
{\an8} <i>Everyone adored him.</i>

312
00:18:43.583 --> 00:18:46.208
{\an8} <i>Except the new senator Severo del Valle.</i>

313
00:18:46.291 --> 00:18:48.333
-You beast from hell!
-[barking]

314
00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:50.666
 <i>-And Nana.</i>
-Out! Get out!

315
00:18:58.000 --> 00:19:00.208
[continues barking]

316
00:19:08.291 --> 00:19:12.375
[pensive music playing]

317
00:19:26.458 --> 00:19:28.833
[birds screeching]

318
00:19:38.833 --> 00:19:40.375
[breath trembling]

319
00:19:40.916 --> 00:19:42.208
Someone's going to die!

320
00:19:45.666 --> 00:19:47.500
-[panting]
-[Nivea] What's wrong. honey?

321
00:19:49.166 --> 00:19:50.166
Someone's about to die.

322
00:19:50.250 --> 00:19:51.541
[Young Ana and Luis] What?

323
00:19:53.333 --> 00:19:56.208
No. my love. Don't worry about it.
That won't happen. all right?

324
00:19:56.666 --> 00:19:57.875
But. wait.

325
00:19:57.958 --> 00:20:00.708
Clara said I was gonna fall off the horse.
and it did happen.

326
00:20:00.791 --> 00:20:02.125
Please do me the honor

327
00:20:02.208 --> 00:20:05.166
of congratulating the new senator
of the republic.

328
00:20:08.708 --> 00:20:10.291
Have you seen a ghost or something?

329
00:20:10.666 --> 00:20:13.541
You better change those sad faces.
Today. we're celebrating.

330
00:20:14.291 --> 00:20:15.416
Sir. more gifts.

331
00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:16.541
This nice liquor

332
00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:19.541
and a roast pig came from your voters
in the south.

333
00:20:19.791 --> 00:20:21.708
I think I should travel soon
to thank them.

334
00:20:21.791 --> 00:20:23.875
-[Nana] Mm-hmm.
-No! Don't go. Dad!

335
00:20:24.541 --> 00:20:25.791
What's wrong with her?

336
00:20:25.875 --> 00:20:27.375
[Nivea] I'll explain later.

337
00:20:27.583 --> 00:20:30.458
That's it. Careful now.
Don't let it fall and get ruined.

338
00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:34.916
Mm! It's a massive creature!

339
00:20:35.000 --> 00:20:36.250
[gasps]

340
00:20:36.791 --> 00:20:39.541
[indistinct chatter]

341
00:20:41.541 --> 00:20:45.041
[piano music playing]

342
00:21:20.666 --> 00:21:21.875
[music stops]

343
00:21:21.958 --> 00:21:23.791
[all applauding]

344
00:21:35.333 --> 00:21:36.708
Severo. please everyone.

345
00:21:36.791 --> 00:21:39.583
if you'd come to hear a few words
from our honorable senator.

346
00:21:40.125 --> 00:21:41.291
Beautiful.

347
00:21:42.708 --> 00:21:44.291
[Nivea] Let's listen to your father.

348
00:21:46.791 --> 00:21:47.958
[Severo] Thank you.

349
00:21:48.708 --> 00:21:51.833
Thank you all for coming here
to celebrate this day with me.

350
00:21:52.416 --> 00:21:54.625
Although I think I should
really be thanking

351
00:21:54.708 --> 00:21:57.000
-the lack of candidates.
-[all laughing]

352
00:21:58.416 --> 00:21:59.458
-Mom?
-Mm-hmm?

353
00:21:59.541 --> 00:22:01.375
I don't want anything bad
to happen to Dad.

354
00:22:01.458 --> 00:22:03.875
No. he'll be just fine. my love.
Don't worry about it.

355
00:22:03.958 --> 00:22:05.458
[Severo] It's a great honor for me

356
00:22:06.250 --> 00:22:09.416
-to represent Liberal Party in Congress.
-Let's go to the back. sweetie.

357
00:22:09.666 --> 00:22:10.833
As you all know.

358
00:22:11.125 --> 00:22:12.583
I have been fortunate enough…

359
00:22:12.666 --> 00:22:15.291
-[continues indistinctly]
-That looks delicious. Ooh!

360
00:22:16.500 --> 00:22:18.708
-Wow! Ooh!
-It has fruit!

361
00:22:19.208 --> 00:22:21.666
-I guess I'll…
-I hope you enjoyed the superb meal

362
00:22:22.166 --> 00:22:24.541
and that you return for seconds
for my family's sake.

363
00:22:24.625 --> 00:22:27.500
or we'll be eating southern style pork
for a week!

364
00:22:27.666 --> 00:22:29.500
[all laughing]

365
00:22:29.791 --> 00:22:30.791
Cheers!

366
00:22:31.333 --> 00:22:32.833
[guests] Cheers!

367
00:22:32.916 --> 00:22:35.250
-[man] Bravo!
-Congratulations.

368
00:22:35.333 --> 00:22:37.750
[all applauding]

369
00:22:41.750 --> 00:22:43.916
-[rain pattering]
-[thunder rumbling]

370
00:22:44.083 --> 00:22:45.500
[Young Clara groaning]

371
00:22:45.583 --> 00:22:47.541
[wind howling]

372
00:22:48.250 --> 00:22:50.541
No! No!

373
00:22:50.916 --> 00:22:52.083
No! No!

374
00:22:52.541 --> 00:22:54.958
Calm down.
Clara. it's all right. calm down.

375
00:23:00.375 --> 00:23:02.041
[sighing]

376
00:23:11.916 --> 00:23:13.833
I don't want anybody to die.

377
00:23:14.166 --> 00:23:16.333
Don't worry.
You were having a nightmare.

378
00:23:16.416 --> 00:23:17.833
Here. try to sleep.

379
00:23:18.458 --> 00:23:20.166
I'm scared. Stay with me.

380
00:23:20.916 --> 00:23:22.541
Of course. Move over.

381
00:23:26.291 --> 00:23:27.625
It's freezing.

382
00:23:33.250 --> 00:23:35.166
You know I'll always be here with you.

383
00:23:36.916 --> 00:23:38.375
Don't you forget.

384
00:23:39.541 --> 00:23:40.750
[chuckles softly]

385
00:23:41.125 --> 00:23:43.833
[taps]

386
00:23:45.041 --> 00:23:46.125
Your hand.

387
00:23:48.208 --> 00:23:50.625
[Rosa coughing]

388
00:23:50.708 --> 00:23:52.541
Aah!

389
00:23:54.250 --> 00:23:55.291
It's a common cold.

390
00:23:55.375 --> 00:23:57.666
[chuckles] See? I told you.

391
00:23:57.750 --> 00:23:59.416
-All good.
-Give her lemonade and sugar

392
00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:01.208
and some liquor
to sweat off the fever.

393
00:24:01.375 --> 00:24:03.875
No. no. Give her the liquor
I was given as a gift.

394
00:24:04.875 --> 00:24:06.500
Thank you. I appreciate it.

395
00:24:07.333 --> 00:24:08.541
I'll walk you to the door.

396
00:24:08.625 --> 00:24:10.541
[somber instrumental music playing]

397
00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:16.750
[grunting]

398
00:24:27.875 --> 00:24:29.166
[Alba] <i>That same day.</i>

399
00:24:29.708 --> 00:24:32.666
 <i>after a long period of isolation</i>
 <i>and effort.</i>

400
00:24:33.625 --> 00:24:35.916
 <i>Esteban Trueba got</i>
 <i>what he was longing for.</i>

401
00:24:37.125 --> 00:24:40.083
[breathing heavily]

402
00:24:44.416 --> 00:24:46.500
[straining]

403
00:24:46.750 --> 00:24:50.833
[Alba] <i>He could finally fulfil his dream</i>
 <i>of marrying Rosa.</i>

404
00:24:53.083 --> 00:24:54.916
[Rosa] Give me the red thread. please.

405
00:24:55.000 --> 00:24:56.458
-Nana!
-[Nana] Hmm?

406
00:24:56.541 --> 00:24:58.958
-Barrabás will be on the tablecloth!
-[Nana gasps]

407
00:24:59.291 --> 00:25:02.125
At any moment. that beast
is going to grow horns!

408
00:25:02.208 --> 00:25:03.583
-And wings.
-[Nana groans]

409
00:25:03.666 --> 00:25:04.958
Thank you.

410
00:25:05.041 --> 00:25:06.416
-[Nana sighs]
-Cheers!

411
00:25:06.875 --> 00:25:08.041
Cheers.

412
00:25:08.125 --> 00:25:09.541
-[chuckles]
-Drink it all.

413
00:25:10.125 --> 00:25:11.208
[Rosa] Mm-hmm.

414
00:25:12.791 --> 00:25:13.833
Ugh.

415
00:25:14.916 --> 00:25:16.416
-Here.
-[Young Clara chuckles]

416
00:25:16.875 --> 00:25:18.166
Thank you. Nana.

417
00:25:18.583 --> 00:25:21.625
[somber instrumental music playing]

418
00:25:23.708 --> 00:25:24.958
[Barrabás barks]

419
00:25:28.291 --> 00:25:33.958
[breathing heavily. shuddering]

420
00:25:59.625 --> 00:26:00.916
[footsteps approaching]

421
00:26:01.000 --> 00:26:03.625
[Nana humming]

422
00:26:11.208 --> 00:26:13.083
[sniffs]

423
00:26:17.750 --> 00:26:19.458
What are you doing there. Clarita?

424
00:26:22.166 --> 00:26:24.000
Why is it so dark? What's wrong?

425
00:26:24.416 --> 00:26:27.375
Oh! Why does it smell so much
like roses in here?

426
00:26:32.416 --> 00:26:33.625
Rosita?

427
00:26:36.333 --> 00:26:37.583
Sweetie?

428
00:26:38.541 --> 00:26:39.750
Rosa?

429
00:26:40.333 --> 00:26:42.625
Oh! Oh. God! [gasps]

430
00:26:46.541 --> 00:26:49.916
[yelling in Spanish]

431
00:26:58.208 --> 00:27:02.375
[somber instrumental music playing]

432
00:27:13.875 --> 00:27:17.958
[breath trembling]

433
00:27:29.250 --> 00:27:31.541
[sobbing]

434
00:27:41.791 --> 00:27:43.000
I'm very sorry.

435
00:27:44.625 --> 00:27:46.625
This wasn't caused by a mere fever.

436
00:27:49.916 --> 00:27:52.291
Did Rosa do something
out of the ordinary?

437
00:27:52.791 --> 00:27:55.291
Maybe she ate something
the others didn't try?

438
00:27:55.375 --> 00:27:58.583
Mm. nothing. No. I don't know.

439
00:27:59.875 --> 00:28:01.125
Um…

440
00:28:01.708 --> 00:28:04.583
that lemonade that you told me to give her

441
00:28:04.666 --> 00:28:07.041
-with a dash of liquor--
-Clarita.

442
00:28:12.375 --> 00:28:14.166
-I think it was me.
-No. No!

443
00:28:15.416 --> 00:28:16.625
No. it wasn't your fault.

444
00:28:16.708 --> 00:28:18.416
You mustn't say that again.
you hear me?

445
00:28:19.166 --> 00:28:20.458
Promise?

446
00:28:23.666 --> 00:28:26.708
[both sobbing]

447
00:28:35.416 --> 00:28:38.500
[somber instrumental music playing]

448
00:28:47.500 --> 00:28:48.916
I wasn't expecting you today.

449
00:28:49.375 --> 00:28:50.458
Good day.

450
00:28:54.833 --> 00:28:55.833
Here.

451
00:29:25.333 --> 00:29:27.416
I suspect
this is what killed your daughter.

452
00:29:29.083 --> 00:29:30.041
What did you say?

453
00:29:30.541 --> 00:29:32.958
I need your authorization
to perform an autopsy.

454
00:29:39.458 --> 00:29:40.958
But do you need to cut her open?

455
00:29:41.458 --> 00:29:43.666
No. Severo. no. Not completely. no.

456
00:29:43.958 --> 00:29:45.333
I won't have to touch her head.

457
00:29:45.750 --> 00:29:48.541
But to do that. I need to take Rosa
to the morgue.

458
00:29:49.125 --> 00:29:49.958
To the morgue?

459
00:29:51.750 --> 00:29:53.375
-Nivea.
-Not to the morgue!

460
00:29:54.166 --> 00:29:55.166
No. no. no. No.

461
00:29:55.250 --> 00:29:56.458
-All right.
-[Doctor] Hmm.

462
00:29:56.541 --> 00:29:59.416
-No one will be taking my daughter away.
-[Severo] Of course not.

463
00:30:00.083 --> 00:30:01.333
Yes. she stays.

464
00:30:03.041 --> 00:30:04.166
Do you swear?

465
00:30:04.500 --> 00:30:07.583
-Swear it. Swear. Severo. Swear to me!
-I do!

466
00:30:11.916 --> 00:30:13.708
-[grunts]
-Nivea!

467
00:30:13.791 --> 00:30:14.958
[sobs]

468
00:30:15.041 --> 00:30:16.750
Ah. my love.

469
00:30:16.875 --> 00:30:18.500
-[Nivea sobbing]
-My love. Nivea. Hey.

470
00:30:20.208 --> 00:30:21.458
[Nivea] Don't touch her.

471
00:30:22.041 --> 00:30:23.458
-Don't touch her.
-Nivea.

472
00:30:23.583 --> 00:30:25.166
Listen. It's all right.

473
00:30:25.250 --> 00:30:27.458
-Nivea. Here. please. drink.
-Please. Nivea. Calm.

474
00:30:27.541 --> 00:30:30.458
Drink. It'll calm your nerves.
Please drink. Just a sip. Just a sip.

475
00:30:38.583 --> 00:30:39.708
Sorry. my love.

476
00:30:40.375 --> 00:30:41.958
I'm doing this for the family.

477
00:30:43.833 --> 00:30:47.166
Nana. tell everyone
to go home for the night.

478
00:30:47.541 --> 00:30:49.916
-Yes. sir.
-And have Clarita sleep with Teresa.

479
00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:50.875
Please. Nana.

480
00:30:51.416 --> 00:30:52.708
She can't sleep alone.

481
00:30:53.458 --> 00:30:54.583
[groans]

482
00:30:55.125 --> 00:30:56.375
[knocking at door]

483
00:31:10.583 --> 00:31:11.666
Severo.

484
00:31:15.666 --> 00:31:17.916
-Good evening--
-[shushes]

485
00:31:19.125 --> 00:31:22.916
[somber instrumental music playing]

486
00:31:25.291 --> 00:31:26.375
Careful.

487
00:31:39.625 --> 00:31:41.666
There was rat poison
in the bottle of liquor.

488
00:31:43.666 --> 00:31:45.666
It was enough to fell an ox.

489
00:31:48.583 --> 00:31:51.833
Now. we only have to prove medically
that it was an assassination.

490
00:31:54.750 --> 00:31:56.333
We need to undress her. Severo.

491
00:32:13.291 --> 00:32:14.541
Forgive me. my child.

492
00:32:33.125 --> 00:32:36.500
[somber instrumental music continues]

493
00:32:40.833 --> 00:32:41.916
[breath trembling]

494
00:32:45.833 --> 00:32:47.666
[Severo] I'm so sorry. I can't stay.

495
00:33:11.958 --> 00:33:13.041
Rosa?

496
00:33:14.041 --> 00:33:16.916
[fire crackling]

497
00:33:18.208 --> 00:33:20.041
-[knocking at door]
-[door opens]

498
00:33:21.583 --> 00:33:22.666
Sir?

499
00:33:23.583 --> 00:33:24.916
Where's our darling Rosa?

500
00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:29.833
Sir?

501
00:33:33.083 --> 00:33:34.125
With the doctor.

502
00:33:35.500 --> 00:33:36.833
-In the kitchen.
-But--

503
00:33:37.791 --> 00:33:39.000
Wait. please stay.

504
00:33:40.125 --> 00:33:41.208
Stay here.

505
00:33:42.208 --> 00:33:45.041
Come have a drink. Please.

506
00:33:48.875 --> 00:33:50.000
Have a seat.

507
00:33:51.541 --> 00:33:52.625
Have a seat.

508
00:34:18.541 --> 00:34:19.583
Thank you.

509
00:34:21.500 --> 00:34:22.708
It's my fault. Nana.

510
00:34:23.291 --> 00:34:24.958
-No--
-I'm afraid it was my fault.

511
00:34:26.166 --> 00:34:27.291
It should be me.

512
00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:28.875
I'm the one who should be dead.

513
00:34:29.375 --> 00:34:30.750
No. don't say that. sir!

514
00:34:30.833 --> 00:34:31.666
Not my Rosa!

515
00:34:33.625 --> 00:34:36.583
[sobbing]

516
00:34:38.458 --> 00:34:39.500
Nana.

517
00:34:40.375 --> 00:34:43.250
[both sobbing]

518
00:34:53.708 --> 00:34:57.000
[intense music playing]

519
00:35:09.000 --> 00:35:10.250
[Doctor] Poor child.

520
00:35:10.333 --> 00:35:11.541
This was meant for Severo.

521
00:35:12.750 --> 00:35:14.041
I have to let him know.

522
00:35:21.333 --> 00:35:22.666
I'm quitting politics

523
00:35:23.333 --> 00:35:24.916
and the Liberal Party as well.

524
00:35:25.875 --> 00:35:27.166
All that rubbish.

525
00:35:29.458 --> 00:35:31.250
[both sigh]

526
00:35:35.708 --> 00:35:39.333
[breathing heavily]

527
00:35:41.250 --> 00:35:44.875
And no one in my family
will ever get mixed up in politics again!

528
00:35:47.541 --> 00:35:50.666
[intense music continues]

529
00:36:34.250 --> 00:36:35.416
[thuds]

530
00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:49.750
[soft instrumental music playing]

531
00:37:10.666 --> 00:37:14.416
[Alba] <i>My Grandma Clara carried</i>
 <i>all the emptiness of the world within her.</i>

532
00:37:16.208 --> 00:37:18.375
 <i>She was utterly swallowed by silence.</i>

533
00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:32.333
 <i>And she kept her voice locked away</i>

534
00:37:33.291 --> 00:37:34.958
 <i>for nine long years.</i>

535
00:37:35.041 --> 00:37:37.583
[typewriter keys clacking]

536
00:37:42.666 --> 00:37:43.750
 <i>Rosa's murder</i>

537
00:37:44.708 --> 00:37:46.958
 <i>was the first of many acts of violence</i>

538
00:37:47.041 --> 00:37:48.833
 <i>that shaped the fate of my family.</i>

539
00:37:48.916 --> 00:37:51.625
[all chanting prayers]

540
00:37:56.958 --> 00:37:59.208
[indistinct conversation]

541
00:38:02.750 --> 00:38:05.583
[Alba] <i>The police tried to follow</i>
 <i>the trail of the poisoned bottle</i>

542
00:38:06.500 --> 00:38:07.375
 <i>but neither they</i>

543
00:38:07.958 --> 00:38:10.791
 <i>nor the detective hired</i>
 <i>by my great-grandfather Severo</i>

544
00:38:11.458 --> 00:38:13.291
 <i>could find the identity of the assassins.</i>

545
00:38:13.375 --> 00:38:16.291
[all chanting prayers]

546
00:38:18.208 --> 00:38:20.375
[Alba] <i>And the shadow</i>
 <i>of vengeance deferred</i>

547
00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:23.666
 <i>has haunted every generation</i>
 <i>that followed.</i>

548
00:38:25.791 --> 00:38:29.583
[all continue chanting prayers]

549
00:38:46.375 --> 00:38:47.750
[Barrabás whimpering]

550
00:38:52.125 --> 00:38:53.625
Clarita?

551
00:38:58.625 --> 00:38:59.833
Clarita. my love?

552
00:39:02.916 --> 00:39:04.750
Come and say goodbye to your sister.

553
00:39:11.000 --> 00:39:11.916
[sighs]

554
00:39:12.625 --> 00:39:15.000
This didn't happen because you said so.

555
00:39:15.958 --> 00:39:19.666
You're able to predict things but. um.
not necessarily prevent them.

556
00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:30.833
My sweet angel.

557
00:39:33.958 --> 00:39:36.583
[Barrabás continues whimpering]

558
00:39:37.125 --> 00:39:38.791
[man] Where are you keeping her?

559
00:39:39.166 --> 00:39:40.583
I want to see her!

560
00:39:43.333 --> 00:39:44.458
Rosa!

561
00:39:45.458 --> 00:39:46.791
Rosa!

562
00:39:48.958 --> 00:39:52.041
[indistinct chatter]

563
00:39:55.708 --> 00:39:59.375
[somber instrumental music playing]

564
00:40:18.583 --> 00:40:19.833
My Rosa.

565
00:40:24.333 --> 00:40:26.416
I'm sorry for not keeping my promise.

566
00:40:27.541 --> 00:40:29.041
I'm sorry it took me so long.

567
00:40:30.583 --> 00:40:32.833
[voice shaking] I'm sorry
it took me so long.

568
00:40:33.833 --> 00:40:34.833
Come with us. Esteban.

569
00:40:42.625 --> 00:40:43.833
[Young Teresa] Nana.

570
00:40:43.916 --> 00:40:46.208
Why can't we go with my dad?

571
00:40:48.208 --> 00:40:49.791
[engine starts]

572
00:40:49.875 --> 00:40:52.375
Well. funerals are men's business.
my love.

573
00:41:03.416 --> 00:41:04.625
[grunts]

574
00:41:05.291 --> 00:41:06.458
[Nivea] Clarita!

575
00:41:11.250 --> 00:41:12.666
[Severo] Stop the car.

576
00:41:12.750 --> 00:41:13.708
Anyway. jump in.

577
00:41:15.416 --> 00:41:16.541
Come here. sweetie.

578
00:41:22.125 --> 00:41:25.500
[somber instrumental music continues]

579
00:41:39.666 --> 00:41:40.750
Are you Clara?

580
00:41:43.791 --> 00:41:46.041
Rosa mentioned you a lot
in her letters.

581
00:41:48.500 --> 00:41:49.666
How old are you?

582
00:41:56.458 --> 00:41:58.375
[Severo] Clara. why won't you
tell him?

583
00:42:00.833 --> 00:42:02.500
[Alba]<i> Clara kept her silence</i>

584
00:42:03.875 --> 00:42:05.666
 <i>but in that moment she knew</i>

585
00:42:06.333 --> 00:42:08.750
 <i>that her fate and Esteban Trueba's</i>

586
00:42:10.208 --> 00:42:12.708
 <i>would be forever bound together.</i>

587
00:42:16.791 --> 00:42:20.250
[exhilarating instrumental music playing]

588
00:43:16.458 --> 00:43:19.791
{\an8}[music continues]

589
00:44:23.916 --> 00:44:28.000
[dramatic music playing]

590
00:44:44.958 --> 00:44:46.041
[music stops]

591
00:44:47.305 --> 00:45:47.359
